<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Scare" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Scare,</orth> (O. Edd. often <emph>scarre</emph>) to frighten: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 1, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.4.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 4, 6</bibl>. <cit><quote>to s. away:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 142</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 3, 66</bibl>. <cit><quote>thy jealous fits have --d thy husband from the use of wits,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 86</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--d my choughs from the chaff,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.630" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 630</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.261" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 261</bibl>. <cit><quote>the spirit of wantonness is --d out of him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.224" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 224</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>s. Troy out of itself,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 10, 21</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--d out of his wits,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 1, 59</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>